claim.claim-text:
71. Apparatus for at least partially restoring the effectiveness of commercial skip systems incorporated in video recorders wherein the effectiveness of the commercial skip systems has been reduced or degraded by modifying an existing signal level in the video signal which is indicative of a commercial, or for enhancing the effectiveness of existing commercial skip systems in which the normal effectiveness has not been reduced or degraded, comprising:
a timing circuit receiving the video signal for providing a timing signal indicative of selected active video lines;
means for supplying a DC restored video signal;
circuit means including detector means for determining a minimum luminance signal value of the DC restored video signal; and
summing means coupled to the circuit means and responsive to the timing circuit for adding to the video signal a negative level shifting voltage corresponding to the minimum luminance signal value, to alter the video signal so as to at least partially restore the degraded commercial skip system or to enhance the effectiveness of the existing commercial skip system.
